	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName> <date>February 22<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 5615</date></p>
				<p>My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I beg to acknowledge<lb/> the receipt of your favor conveying the<lb/> resolution of the &#8220;Board of Managers&#8221; of<lb/> the Congregation over which you so<lb/> ably preside&#44; in which I am honored<lb/> with the appointment &#8220;to perform the<lb/> Marriage Ceremony&#8221; for my Respected<lb/> friend and colleague the <persName>Revd I Morais</persName><lb/> I need not say how much pleasure<lb/> it affords me to accept of this honor<lb/> and how sincere my wishes are for the<lb/> happiness of the Bride and Bridegroom<lb/> not only&#44; but also for the continued<lb/> prosperity of your congregation&#44; over<lb/> which&#44; this important step on the<lb/> part of their worthy <add>Hebrew</add> can not fail<lb/> to exercise a most beneficial result.</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I shall take the earliest oppor<lb/>tunity to lay the invitation before my<lb/> Board of Trustees the result of which<lb/> I trust will be satisfactory and which<lb/> I shall take pleasure to communicate</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mrs Lyons</persName> joins with me in<lb/> kind regards to yourself and Lady<lb/> She intends&#44; God willing to avail her<lb/>&#45;self of this opportunity to visit<lb/> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> when she will personally<lb/> make her acknowledgments for your kind<lb/> remembrance of her wishes.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I remain with due respect</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">My Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">J I Lyons</persName></p>
				<p><addressee>Abm Hart Esqr</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
		</body>
